commit.message:
Remove dependency on `errors`

closes #8
Weaken upper bound on `text` to support text-2
Convert to cabal project and use GitHub actions for CI

Fix build tool name typo in .cabal file

I’m not certain how this ever worked, but I guess it was previously
unchecked.
Update stack configuration for CI

Add some (fairly loose) upper bounds on all dependencies

These packages are pretty foundational, and our dependency on them is
very minimal, so it’s unlikely that most updates will break them, but
the recent base16-bytestring-1.0.0.0 breakage highlights the dangers of
not even constraining the supermajor version. This adds a little more
safety without being terribly constraining.

Also, check in the .cabal file to play nicer with cabal-install.
Support for `base16-bytestring-1.0.0.0` (#11)

commit.message:
Add `build-tool-depends` for `hspec-discovery`

Otherwise there is no metadata that this executable is needed, and
`cabal new-build` (and maybe soon Nix) will fail. OTOH this also 
means the regular `build-depends` isn't needed, and indeed this is
important for cross compilation.

Add `build-tool-depends` for `hspec-discovery`

Otherwise there is no metadata that this executable is needed, and
`cabal new-build` (and maybe soon Nix) will fail. OTOH this also 
means the regular `build-depends` isn't needed, and indeed this is
important for cross compilation.

commit.message: Update .travis.yml to build against GHC 8.2
Add Travis CI
Reorganize the documentation to be more usefully ordered
fix decodeConvertText typo in the documentation example
Retroactively update the CHANGELOG for 0.3.0
Add support for Base16 and Base64 encodings
Update the README to be correct for 0.2.0

Split ConvertText into convertText and decodeConvertText

Unforunately, Haskell’s typeclass resolution mechanisms make it pretty
much impossible for the unified ConvertText system with overlapping
instances to work. Specifically, FromText (Maybe Foo) instances will not
properly resolve, because they would pick the overlapping DecodeText
instance instead of the simpler ToText/FromText instance.
Remove unused piece of test code
Add a link to the hackage docs in the README
Mark Data.Text.Conversions as Safe
Initial commit
